  <front>
    <title>Extended Ethernet Frame Size Support</title>
    <seriesInfo name="Internet-Draft" value="draft-kaplan-isis-ext-eth-02"/>
    <author initials="M. D." surname="O'Dell" fullname="Michael D. O'Dell"/>
    <author initials="J." surname="Kaplan" fullname="Jed Kaplan"/>
    <author initials="J." surname="Hayes" fullname="John Hayes"/>
    <author initials="P." surname="Singh" fullname="P.J. Singh"/>
    <author initials="D." surname="Morrell" fullname="Daemon Morrell"/>
    <author initials="J." surname="Hsu" fullname="Jennifer Hsu"/>
    <date day="26" month="May" year="2000"></date>
    <abstract>
      <t>This document presents an extension to current Ethernet Frame 
standards to support payloads greater than 1500 Bytes for Ethernet_II
and 802.3 frames. This is useful for Gigabit Ethernet technology, 
providing a means to carry large MTU packets without fragmentation 
over a high-speed broadcast network.
	 </t>
    </abstract>
